  "prompt": "I was booking ticket from IRCTC but due to technical problem, I fail to book the tckt, bt amt got debited from account. By when would that b refunded?",
  "response": "Okay, I understand. It's frustrating when that happens. Here's a breakdown of the typical refund timeline for IRCTC when a transaction fails but the amount is debited, and what you can do to follow up:\n\n**Typical Refund Timeline:**\n\n*   **IRCTC Standard Refund Timeframe:** Generally, IRCTC states that refunds for failed transactions can take **4-7 business days** to be credited back to your original payment method (the account from which the money was debited).  However, depending on your bank and the payment method used, it can sometimes take a little longer.\n*   **UPI Transactions:** Refunds for transactions made through UPI are usually faster, potentially within 1-3 business days.\n*   **Weekends and Holidays:** Keep in mind that weekends and bank holidays can delay the processing time.\n\n**What You Should Do Now:**\n\n1.  **Check Your Transaction History on IRCTC:**\n\n    *   Log in to your IRCTC account.\n    *   Go to the \"My Transactions\" section.\n    *   Look for the transaction in question.  It should show a status like \"Transaction Failed\" or \"Payment Failed.\"\n    *   There might be a refund status or a reference number associated with the refund. Note this down.\n\n2.  **Wait a Few Days (If You Haven't Already):**\n\n    *   Give it the standard 4-7 business days. Sometimes the refund processes without any intervention needed.\n\n3.  **Check Your Bank/Payment Method Statement:**\n\n    *   Regularly check your bank account statement or the transaction history of your credit card/debit card/UPI app to see if the refund has been credited.\n\n4.  **If the Refund is Delayed (After 7 Business Days):**\n\n    *   **Contact IRCTC Customer Care:** This is the most important step.\n        *   **IRCTC Customer Care Number:** 0755-6610661, 0755-4090600\n        *   **IRCTC iPay (Payment Gateway) Customer Care:** 0755-6610661, 0755-4090600\n        *   **IRCTC Email:** etickets@irctc.co.in\n        *   **Include the following information in your communication:**\n            *   Your IRCTC User ID\n            *   Transaction Date and Time\n            *   Transaction Amount\n            *   PNR (if generated, even if the ticket wasn't confirmed)\n            *   Transaction ID or Reference Number (from your bank statement or IRCTC transaction history)\n            *   A brief explanation of the problem (failed transaction, amount debited)\n\n5.  **Escalate if Necessary:**\n\n    *   If you don't get a satisfactory response from IRCTC customer care within a reasonable time (e.g., a few days), you can escalate the issue.\n    *   **IRCTC Grievance Redressal:** Look for a \"Grievance\" or \"Complaint\" section on the IRCTC website. You can usually file a formal complaint online.\n\n6.  **Consider Your Bank/Payment Provider:**\n\n    *   If IRCTC is unresponsive or unable to resolve the issue, you can also contact your bank or payment provider (e.g., the credit card company, UPI app provider). They may be able to investigate the transaction and initiate a chargeback if necessary.  This is usually a last resort.\n\n**Important Points:**\n\n*   **Keep Records:** Keep screenshots of your IRCTC transaction history, bank statements showing the debit, and any communication you have with IRCTC.\n*   **Be Patient:**  Refund processes can sometimes take time, so be persistent but polite when communicating with customer service.\n*   **Act Promptly:** Don't delay in contacting IRCTC if the refund is not received within the expected timeframe.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to track down your refund and get the issue resolved. Good luck!\n",
